question:
A logistics problem dealing with the transportation of soybeans from multiple supply terminals to various destinations, with routes connecting terminals and destinations. Each route has associated transportation costs and each destination has a specific demand to be met, while each terminal has a limited supply. PROBLEM TYPE: LP

INPUT FORMAT:

{
    "routes": [
       {
        "start": i,
        "end": j,
        "C": Cost_{i,j},
       }
    ],
    "demand": [
        {
            "destination": l,
            "D": Demand_{l}
        }
    ],
    "supply": [
        {
            "terminal": k,
            "S": Supply_{k}
        }
    ]
}

OBJECTIVE: What quantity of soybeans should they transport from source to destination to minimize transportation costs? Number of terminals is 3. Number of destinations is 4. Cost of transportation for route from terminal i to destination j is [[34, 49, 17, 26], [52, 64, 23, 14], [20, 28, 12, 17]]. Demand at each destination is [65, 70, 50, 45]. Supply at each terminal is [150, 100, 100].  Transported quantity from terminal to destination is non-negative. Transported quantity from each terminal cannot exceed its supply. Transported quantity to each destination must meet its demand.  Minimize the total transportation costs of delivering soybeans from terminals to destinations.
